name: trawler construction, steel | trawler, steel | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/17856/documentation

This dataset represents the construction of steel trawlers, per 1000 kg of light ship weight, based on data from Peru (2004-3013), corresponding to 9 vessels (from a fleet of 54) for which data was avilable with different levels of detail. Specific data for specific inventory items may be based on sub-samples for which detailed data was available. Vessel dimensions: 34 - 275 m3 (16 - 34 m length).;System boundaries and relation between activities

Construction of vessels, including provision of all materials and work

Batteries are excluded, as they do not exist in the database
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/03:Fishing and aquaculture/031:Fishing/0311:Marine fishing

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from Peru, extrapolated to global (GLO)
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Peru features various shipyards and relevant ship-building and ship-retrofitting expertise.

exchanges.description: Construction of a steel trawler, per 1000 kg of light ship weight (LSW). Regressions based on mainly primary data were created to relate the weight of each inventory item to a purse seiner's LSW, adjusted for trawler's gear. The list of inventory items (granularity) contribute >95% of environmental impacts, as described in the reference publication.
